----------------------------------------
For Intalling Git in Ubuntu
----------------------------------------

Use the apt package management tools to update your local package index.

$ sudo apt update

After the update, download Git with the following command

$ sudo apt install git

You would be prompted to enter your password. Enter your password and proceed

In order to check which version of git is install in your system or whether it is installed correctly or not, run the following command:

$ git --version

You should get an output similar to this:

git version 2.17.1

------------------------------------------
For setting up Git in Ubuntu
------------------------------------------

In your terminal, type the following command

1) $ git config --global user.name "your_username"

Give your username without double apostrophes.

2) Next type the following command

$ git config --global user.email "your_emailid"

Give your emailid without double apostrophes.

The username is the user name of your github account in www.github.com

The email id is that email id which is associated with your github account.

 
